node.text:
Kamdhenu Cow and Calf Idol is the sacred wish-cow that grants all your wishes and desires. Kamdhenu cow is the mother of divine qualities and on earth, it is equivalent to Goddess. Kamdhenu cow idol along with its calf is the symbol of prosperity and Vatsalya (love that a mother feels for a child). Every part of Kamdhenu’s body has a religious significance. Its four legs symbolize the four Vedas, and its teats the four Purusharthas. Its horns symbolize the Gods, its face symbolize the Sun and the Moon, its shoulders Agni and its legs the Himalayas.
.
.
.
.
